  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Identify the threshold which the handgrip strenght can be used as a screening test of
      sarcopenia.

      Handgrip strenght can be used in daily clinical practice to screen patients having sarcopenia
      to improve treatment and quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A cross-sectional multicentre study will be performed in hospital and retirement houses on
      patients ages 75 years old or more.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
